This program is terminal rogue-like game. All features prior to assignment 1.10 are operational. Ranged combat has been implemented. If a ranged weapon is equipped, 'r' pulls up a menu to select a visible monster to attack. Capital letters are used to select a monster. Poison bombs were also implemented.  In order to cast the bomb spell, 'p' brings up a menu similar to 'r'. Bombs hit the selected monster for full damage and any adjacent monsters for half. Dodge and defense have been implemented. defense lowers damage taken based on a formula while dodge provides a chance to completely evades an attack.  Dodge caps at 95%. Both monsters and pc have these stats. Items affect these stats for the player. ‘c’ now also displays the current dodge and defense. Ranged attacks have a higher chance of being dodged. The magic bomb cannot be defended or dodged.